Reinforcement Learning, Theory. 

Reinforcement learning is present in the paper as the algorithm presented is an on-line investment algorithm that learns from the market outcomes and adjusts the portfolio accordingly. The algorithm employs a multiplicative update rule derived using a framework introduced by Kivinen and Warmuth. 

Theory is also present in the paper as the authors present a theoretical framework for their algorithm and provide mathematical proofs for its performance. They also compare their algorithm to other existing algorithms and provide theoretical explanations for the differences in performance.
